<exercise>
<rubric>Complete the sentences with the comparative form of the adjective in orange.</rubric>
<!--<audio>content/pdCCR1/assets/dialogue.mp3</audio>-->
<questions>
<question>
<sentence>I don't like the new computer system.</sentence>
</question><question>
<sentence>Really? I think it's [#] than the old one.</sentence>
<answers>
<answer>easier</answer>
<answer>EASIER</answer>
</answers>
<hint pos="right">easy</hint>
</question><question>
<sentence>I don't think so. I think it's [#].</sentence>
<answers>
<answer>more difficult</answer>
<answer>MORE DIFFICULT</answer>
</answers>
<hint pos="right">difficult</hint>
</question><question>
<sentence>I don't have any problems with it.</sentence>
</question><question>
<sentence>Because you're [#] with computers than me.</sentence>
<answers>
<answer>more experienced</answer>
<answer>MORE EXPERIENCED</answer>
</answers>
<hint pos="right">experienced</hint>
</question><question>
<sentence>That's true. But I do think the new system is [#] than the old one.</sentence>
<answers>
<answer>better</answer>
<answer>BETTER</answer>
</answers>
<hint pos="right">good</hint>
</question><question>
<sentence>How is it better?</sentence>
</question><question>
<sentence>Well, it's [#] than the old system. Everyone says that.</sentence>
<answers>
<answer>faster</answer>
<answer>FASTER</answer>
</answers>
<hint pos="right">fast</hint>
</question>
</questions></exercise>
